==English==

===Etymology===
Latin "new" (star)

===Noun===
'''nova''' (''plural'' [[novae]])

#{{astronomy}} [[Star]] which [[explode]]s, increasing its brightness by hundreds of thousands of times, then usually reverts to its original luminosity. See also [[Supernova]]

